<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3831654>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Pulvinaria araliae Shinji, 1935, neotype adult female. ANT, antenna; AP, anal plate; DMD, dorsal microduct; DS, dorsal seta; DTD, dorsal tubular duct; LG, leg; MP, multilocular pore; MS, marginal seta; POP, preopercular pores; SDP, spiracular disc pore; SSP, stigmatic spines; VMD, ventral microduct; VTD, ventral tubular ducts of types I–III. Scale bars: 200 µm for ANT and LG; 100 µm for AP; 50 µm for MS and SSP; 10 µm for others." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3831654/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

